bilingual.source: The outdoor concert was a huge success.
bilingual.target: 那场户外的音乐会非常成功。

bilingual.source: They organized an outdoor barbecue for the weekend.
bilingual.target: 他们为周末组织了一次户外的烧烤。

bilingual.source: She prefers outdoor sports like hiking and cycling.
bilingual.target: 她更喜欢像徒步和骑行这样的户外的运动。

bilingual.source: We enjoy many outdoor activities during the summer.
bilingual.target: 我们在夏天喜欢进行许多户外的活动。

bilingual.source: The restaurant has a beautiful outdoor seating area.
bilingual.target: 那家餐厅有一个漂亮的户外的座位区。
找人帮忙做户外的工作。
天文是户外的亲近大自然的爱好。

bilingual.source: The outdoor concert was a great success!
bilingual.target: 那场户外的演唱会很成功!

bilingual.source: Well then, let's go to an outdoor symphony concert.
bilingual.target: 那么，我们去一个户外的交响乐演奏会。

list.abstract: outdoor（英 [ˈaʊtdɔː]，美 [ˈaʊtdɔːr]），英语单词。指的是户外的；室外的；喜欢户外活动的。相关短语搭配有outdoor activity、outdoor pursuits、outdoor pool。例句有“The report includes both indoor and outdoor air pollution.（该报告包括室内和室外空气污染。）” 相关近义词有out of door，相关反义词有indoor。

yingyinNormal.en: This 6,400 acre outdoor film set is now the world's biggest.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个二十五万平方千米的电影外景地，体量之大冠绝全球。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe we'll become famous artists. We'll go to Paris, drink coffee in outdoor cafes. How do I look?
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许有一天我们会变成著名的艺术家，我们就去巴黎，在户外咖啡馆喝咖啡，我看起来如何？

yingyinNormal.en: To cope with a 30 million annual visitors, the Chinese have built the world's highest outdoor elevator.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了满足每年三千万人次的游客，中国修建了世界上最高的户外电梯。

yingyinNormal.en: At the end of the day, let the outdoor escalators on Central carry you up to the midlevel neighborhoods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 日落时份，不妨乘搭中环的户外电梯走到中半山区。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, if you'll excuse me, I'm going to go clean up. Outdoor wedding. I know what I'll be using that cliff for.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在请允许我去清洗一下。露天婚礼。我知道我会用那悬崖来干什么。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, picture this: a beautiful outdoor concert. Now, as a human, I appreciate Beethoven. As a fungus, I have a terrific view, growing out of a towering maple tree. And no thank you, expensive concessions. Because as an algae, I'll just snack on this sun light.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没问题，试想一下：一场高雅的户外音乐会，作为人类，我能够欣赏贝多芬的音乐；作为菌类，我能够沿着耸立的枫树生长，以获得最棒的视野；我也无需花钱买高昂的酒水，因为作为藻类，我以光合作用维生。
